unittitle_ssm: Tamiment Library and Robert F. Wagner Labor Archives Collection of Anarchism Serials
abstract_ssm: The Tamiment Library and Robert F. Wagner Labor Archives Collection of Anarchism Serials contains over 300 titles on anarchist movements and philosophies in the United States, Italy, Spain, France, and other countries.  The collection dates between 1890 and 2010, with the bulk of the material dating from the 1960s through 1990s.  Topics include anarchist theories and principles regarding economic, political, social, and labor issues in the United States and other countries; anarcho-syndicalist movements in Europe in the 20th century; and feminist movements within anarchist organizations.
